#import "../../book.typ": *
// ===================== PSALM 98 =====================
#startprayer("Psalm 98 · Mizmor Shiru", "מִזְמוֹר שִׁירוּ")
#stanza("Mizmor, shiru l’Adonai shir chadash, ki nifla’ot asah; hoshi’ah lo y’mino uzro’a kodsho. Hodi’a Adonai yeshu’ato, l’einei hagoyim gila tzidkato. Zachar chasdo ve’emunato l’veit Yisra’el, ra’u chol afsei aretz et yeshu’at Eloheinu.",
  "מִזְמוֹר שִׁירוּ לַיְיָ שִׁיר חָדָשׁ כִּי־נִפְלָאוֹת עָשָׂה הוֹשִׁיעָה־לּוֹ יְמִינוֹ וּזְרוֹעַ קׇדְשׁוֹ. הוֹדִיעַ יְיָ יְשׁוּעָתוֹ לְעֵינֵי הַגּוֹיִם גִּלָּה צִדְקָתוֹ. זָכַר חַסְדּוֹ וֶאֱמוּנָתוֹ לְבֵית יִשְׂרָאֵל רָאוּ כׇל־אַפְסֵי־אָרֶץ אֵת יְשׁוּעַת אֱלֹהֵינוּ.", label:"Sung")
#stanza("Hari’u l’Adonai kol ha’aretz, pitzchu v’ran’nu v’zameru. Zam’ru l’Adonai b’chinor, b’chinor v’kol zimrah. Bachatzotz’rot v’kol shofar, hari’u lifnei haMelech Adonai.",
  "הָרִיעוּ לַיְיָ כׇּל־הָאָרֶץ פִּצְחוּ וְרַנְּנוּ וְזַמֵּרוּ. זַמְּרוּ לַיְיָ בְּכִנּוֹר בְּכִנּוֹר וְקוֹל זִמְרָה. בַּחֲצֹצְרוֹת וְקוֹל שׁוֹפָר הָרִיעוּ לִפְנֵי הַמֶּלֶךְ יְיָ.")
#stanza("Yir’am hayam umlo’o, tevel v’yosh’vei vah. N’harot yimcha’u chaf, yachad harim y’ranenu. Lifnei Adonai, ki va lishpot ha’aretz; yishpot tevel b’tzedek, v’amim b’meisharim.",
  "יִרְעַם הַיָּם וּמְלֹאוֹ תֵּבֵל וְיֹשְׁבֵי בָהּ. נְהָרוֹת יִמְחֲאוּ־כָף יַחַד הָרִים יְרַנֵּנוּ. לִפְנֵי־יְיָ כִּי בָא לִשְׁפֹּט הָאָרֶץ יִשְׁפֹּט־תֵּבֵל בְּצֶדֶק וְעַמִּים בְּמֵישָׁרִים.")
#eng("Sing a new song, for wonders have been done: freedom won by an outstretched arm. That saving power is made known to all the nations, and steady, faithful love kept for the house of Israel — until the very ends of the earth have seen the rescue our God brings.")
#eng("Shout out, all the earth — burst into song, break open with music! Make music on the harp, with the harp and the sound of singing; with trumpets and the call of the shofar, raise a shout before the One who reigns over all.")
#engn("Let the sea thunder and all that fills it, the world and all who dwell in it. Let the rivers clap their hands, let the mountains sing together — for the One who comes to set the earth right, to judge the world with justice and the peoples with fairness.",
  [Here even nature is drawn into the choir: the rivers clap their hands and the mountains sing, for the God who comes to judge the earth with righteousness is cause for all creation to rejoice, not to tremble. In this vision justice is not punishment but relief — the setting-right that everything alive has been waiting for.])

// ===================== PSALM 99 =====================
#startprayer("Psalm 99 · Adonai Malach", "יְיָ מָלָךְ")
#stanza("Adonai malach, yirg’zu amim; yoshev k’ruvim, tanut ha’aretz. Adonai b’Tziyon gadol, v’ram hu al kol ha’amim. Yodu shimcha gadol v’nora — kadosh hu.",
  "יְיָ מָלָךְ יִרְגְּזוּ עַמִּים יֹשֵׁב כְּרוּבִים תָּנוּט הָאָרֶץ. יְיָ בְּצִיּוֹן גָּדוֹל וְרָם הוּא עַל־כׇּל־הָעַמִּים. יוֹדוּ שִׁמְךָ גָּדוֹל וְנוֹרָא קָדוֹשׁ הוּא.")
#stanza("V’oz melech mishpat ahev, atah konanta meisharim; mishpat utz’daka b’Ya’akov atah asita. Rom’mu Adonai Eloheinu, v’hishtachavu lahadom raglav — kadosh hu.",
  "וְעֹז מֶלֶךְ מִשְׁפָּט אָהֵב אַתָּה כּוֹנַנְתָּ מֵישָׁרִים מִשְׁפָּט וּצְדָקָה בְּיַעֲקֹב אַתָּה עָשִׂיתָ. רוֹמְמוּ יְיָ אֱלֹהֵינוּ וְהִשְׁתַּחֲווּ לַהֲדֹם רַגְלָיו קָדוֹשׁ הוּא.")
#stanza("Moshe v’Aharon b’chohanav, ush’mu’el b’kor’ei sh’mo — kor’im el Adonai, v’hu ya’anem. B’amud anan y’daber aleihem; shamru edotav, v’chok natan lamo.",
  "מֹשֶׁה וְאַהֲרֹן בְּכֹהֲנָיו וּשְׁמוּאֵל בְּקֹרְאֵי שְׁמוֹ קֹרִאים אֶל־יְיָ וְהוּא יַעֲנֵם. בְּעַמּוּד עָנָן יְדַבֵּר אֲלֵיהֶם שָׁמְרוּ עֵדֹתָיו וְחֹק נָתַן־לָמוֹ.")
#stanza("Adonai Eloheinu, atah anitam; El nose hayita lahem, v’nokem al alilotam. Rom’mu Adonai Eloheinu, v’hishtachavu l’har kodsho — ki kadosh Adonai Eloheinu.",
  "יְיָ אֱלֹהֵינוּ אַתָּה עֲנִיתָם אֵל נֹשֵׂא הָיִיתָ לָהֶם וְנֹקֵם עַל־עֲלִילוֹתָם. רוֹמְמוּ יְיָ אֱלֹהֵינוּ וְהִשְׁתַּחֲווּ לְהַר קׇדְשׁוֹ כִּי־קָדוֹשׁ יְיָ אֱלֹהֵינוּ.")
#eng("The Holy One reigns — let the peoples tremble; enthroned on the cherubim — let the earth shake. Great in Zion, high above all peoples: let them praise Your name, great and awesome — holy is the One.")
#eng("Mighty One who loves justice, You who founded fairness — justice and righteousness in Jacob are Your doing. Exalt HaShem our God and bow low at the place where holiness rests — holy is the One.")
#eng("Moses and Aaron among the priests, and Samuel among those who called on the Name — they called, and they were answered. From a pillar of cloud came the answer; they kept the teachings, the law that was given to them.")
#engn("HaShem our God, You answered them; You were forgiving to them, holding them accountable for their deeds. Exalt HaShem our God, and bow toward the holy mountain — for holy is HaShem our God.",
  [Three times this psalm calls God kadosh — holy — yet it grounds that holiness not in remoteness but in answered prayer, recalling Moses, Aaron, and Samuel, who called and were answered. It deliberately names Samuel, not a priest by birth, alongside the priests — a hint that access to the Holy is opened by the honesty of one’s calling, not by pedigree.])

// ===================== PSALM 29 =====================
#startprayer("Psalm 29 · Mizmor l’David", "מִזְמוֹר לְדָוִד")
#stanza("Mizmor l’David. Havu l’Adonai b’nei elim, havu l’Adonai kavod va’oz. Havu l’Adonai k’vod sh’mo, hishtachavu l’Adonai b’hadrat kodesh.",
  "מִזְמוֹר לְדָוִד הָבוּ לַיְיָ בְּנֵי אֵלִים הָבוּ לַיְיָ כָּבוֹד וָעֹז. הָבוּ לַיְיָ כְּבוֹד שְׁמוֹ הִשְׁתַּחֲווּ לַיְיָ בְּהַדְרַת־קֹדֶשׁ.")
#stanza("Kol Adonai al hamayim, El hakavod hir’im, Adonai al mayim rabim. Kol Adonai bako’ach, kol Adonai behadar. Kol Adonai shover arazim, vay’shaber Adonai et arzei haL’vanon. Vayarkidem k’mo egel, L’vanon v’Siryon k’mo ven r’emim.",
  "קוֹל יְיָ עַל־הַמָּיִם אֵל־הַכָּבוֹד הִרְעִים יְיָ עַל־מַיִם רַבִּים. קוֹל־יְיָ בַּכֹּחַ קוֹל יְיָ בֶּהָדָר. קוֹל יְיָ שֹׁבֵר אֲרָזִים וַיְשַׁבֵּר יְיָ אֶת־אַרְזֵי הַלְּבָנוֹן. וַיַּרְקִידֵם כְּמוֹ־עֵגֶל לְבָנוֹן וְשִׂרְיֹן כְּמוֹ בֶן־רְאֵמִים.")
#stanza("Kol Adonai chotzev lahavot esh. Kol Adonai yachil midbar, yachil Adonai midbar Kadesh. Kol Adonai y’cholel ayalot vayechesof y’arot, uvheichalo kulo omer kavod.",
  "קוֹל־יְיָ חֹצֵב לַהֲבוֹת אֵשׁ. קוֹל יְיָ יָחִיל מִדְבָּר יָחִיל יְיָ מִדְבַּר קָדֵשׁ. קוֹל יְיָ יְחוֹלֵל אַיָּלוֹת וַיֶּחֱשֹׂף יְעָרוֹת וּבְהֵיכָלוֹ כֻּלּוֹ אֹמֵר כָּבוֹד.")
#stanza("Adonai lamabul yashav, vayeshev Adonai melech l’olam. Adonai oz l’amo yiten, Adonai y’varech et amo vashalom.",
  "יְיָ לַמַּבּוּל יָשָׁב וַיֵּשֶׁב יְיָ מֶלֶךְ לְעוֹלָם. יְיָ עֹז לְעַמּוֹ יִתֵּן יְיָ יְבָרֵךְ אֶת־עַמּוֹ בַשָּׁלוֹם.", label:"Sung")
#eng("A song of David. Give to the Holy One, you children of the mighty — give glory and strength. Give the glory due to the Name; bow before the One in the beauty of holiness.")
#eng("The voice of the Holy One over the waters — the God of glory thunders, over the vast waters. The voice, in power; the voice, in splendor. The voice shatters cedars, splinters the cedars of Lebanon, makes the mountains skip like a calf, Lebanon and Sirion like a young wild ox.")
#engn([The voice carves out flames of fire; the voice makes the wilderness shudder, shakes the wilderness of Kadesh; the voice sends the deer into labor and strips the forests bare — and in the sanctuary, everything cries out: #emph[kavod]. Above the flood the Holy One was enthroned, and reigns as sovereign of all, forever. May the Holy One give strength to this people; may the Holy One bless this people with peace.],
  [Seven times this psalm thunders kol Adonai, the voice of the Holy One, across the waters, and the Divine Name appears eighteen times — an ancient storm-poem the Safed mystics set as the sixth of the weekday psalms and the crown of them all, so that the roar of the world resolves at last into the single word that ends it: shalom, peace.])
